timeline.summary: This document is an email return concurrence form (ED-1036 Rev. 10-16-2009) related to a death investigation, Case ID #: 90A-NY-3151227. The email concerns Jeffrey Epstein as a victim and was drafted on 09/05/2019. It was approved by SSA and marked as UNSUB(S).

This document is an unofficial FBI record concerning the death investigation of Jeffrey Epstein. It includes documents provided by DIG SA from MCC, specifically: L-Tier Daily Logs for August 9 and 10, a Weekly Signature Sheet for weeks of 7/28 and 8/4, an Incident Report from July 23, a Suicide Timeline (8/9-8/13), a memo regarding Epstein remains, a memo regarding an Epstein phone call (8/9), and Chain of Custody Logs from MCC. The record was received on October 16, 2009.

This document is an official FBI record regarding a death investigation. The record includes phone records for MCC Caller Station 6317, provided by the Office of Inspector General (OIG) on October 16, 2009. The case ID is 90A-NY-3151227, involving Jeffrey Epstein as a victim and classified as an UNSUB(S) death investigation.

This document is a redacted FBI import form, FD-1036, related to a death investigation involving Jeffrey Epstein. The form was drafted on 2025-12-27 and references an OIG referral (CIA-2019-05324) received on 10-16-2009, categorized as “Other.” The case ID is 90A-NY-3151227, noting Epstein as a victim and the investigation’s focus. It includes a facial record dated 09/23/2019.

This document is an import form related to a case file (90A-NY-3151227) concerning the July 23, 2019 suicide attempt of Jeffrey Epstein. The form includes a photograph of a homemade rope taken from the scene. The document identifies Jeffrey Epstein as a victim and indicates an ongoing death investigation. It references serial 81 within the case file.

This document is an FBI Import Form (Fp-1023) dated October 19, 2020, concerning a Type 3 Assessment titled "2020 Election Influence Threat – FBI Los Angeles Area of Responsibility." The assessment investigates potential foreign influence, specifically from Israel, Russia, and the UAE, targeting U.S. officials. Two attached documents, labeled “DELTA” and “ETA,” are included as enclosures. The document is marked as UNCLASSIFIED//FOUO.

This document is a letter from the U.S. Department of Justice, Southern District of New York, to Montell Figgins regarding the case of United States v. Michael Thomas (No. 19 Cr. 830). It provides additional discovery materials subject to a protective order. The materials include arrest documentation, FBI documents (including import forms, laboratory examination requests, and process reports), witness statements, an anonymized index, and US Marshals Service intake records.  Additionally, the government is providing information regarding disciplinary actions taken against inmate Tony McClam at the MCC and MDC, and a list of inmate deaths over the last ten years at those institutions. All materials are classified as "Confidential" and “Attorney’s Eyes Only.”

This document is a letter from the U.S. Department of Justice, Southern District of New York, to legal counsel regarding the case of *United States v. Tom Noel No. 19 Cr. 830*. It provides additional discovery materials as per Rule 16(a) of the Federal Rules of Criminal Procedure, subject to a protective order. The materials include arrest documentation, FBI documents (including import forms, laboratory examination requests, and process reports), witness statements, and information from the US Marshals Service and the Bureau of Prisons (BOP). The BOP information details disciplinary actions related to log entry falsification and lists inmate deaths over the last ten years at the MCC and MDC institutions. Access to this information is restricted and designated as “Protected Materials.”
